Legend

  • WNS: Worst Negative Slack (ns)
  • TNS: Total Negative Slack (ns)
  • NVP: Number of Violating Paths
  • DSR Skew: DSR Mux Clock Skew (picoseconds) - Lower is better
  • Total Internal: Sum of all internal timing groups (excludes FEEDTHROUGH/REGIN/REGOUT)

Color Coding

  • Green: Positive slack (meets timing) / Excellent DSR skew (<=10ps)
  • Red/Orange: Negative slack (timing violations) / Unacceptable DSR skew (>10ps)

Column Order

  • 1. DSR Skew: Physical design metric (same for all scenarios)
  • 2. Total Internal: Overall internal timing health
  • 3. Internal Groups: Individual clock domains (i1_clk, i2_clk, etc.)
  • 4. External Groups: FEEDTHROUGH/REGIN/REGOUT (relaxed, always 0)
